MY website Development


Using Visual Studio code as IDE

Steps:
1. Installed Node package from https://nodejs.org/en/download/ and selected macOS Installer
2. After following the screen instruction, nodejs was successfully installed.

checking versions with command
1. "node --version" ----- v14.16.1
2. "npm --version" ------ 6.14.12

For mac , you might get access error -- for accessing node packages, so execute the bellow command 

check the path of npm folder by "npm config get prefix" and it will be generally   -- "/usr/local"

"sudo chown -R $(whoami) $(npm config get prefix)/{lib/node_modules,bin,share}"


To install the Angular CLI, in a terminal or command prompt type:

npm install -g @angular/cli

version is 11.2.10



